# ChroPlexiGnosis Project Structure

This Flutter project follows a modular architecture with clear separation of concerns:

- **Entry Point**: [lib/main.dart](mdc:lib/main.dart) initializes the app and sets up themes, routes and services.

- **Core Layer**: The `lib/core` directory contains foundational elements like constants, themes, and utilities.
  - Colors and styling are defined in [lib/core/constants/colors.dart](mdc:lib/core/constants/colors.dart)
  - App theme is configured in [lib/core/themes/app_theme.dart](mdc:lib/core/themes/app_theme.dart)

- **Models Layer**: The `lib/models` directory contains data classes that represent game entities.
  - Game units (board pieces) are defined in [lib/models/game_unit.dart](mdc:lib/models/game_unit.dart)
  - Level configurations are in [lib/models/level.dart](mdc:lib/models/level.dart)

- **Screens Layer**: The `lib/screens` directory contains all UI screens, organized by feature.
  - The home screen is in [lib/screens/home/home_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/home/home_screen.dart)
  - The game board is in [lib/screens/game/game_screen.dart](mdc:lib/screens/game/game_screen.dart)

- **Services Layer**: The `lib/services` directory contains business logic and data services.
  - Game mechanics are implemented in [lib/services/game_logic.dart](mdc:lib/services/game_logic.dart)
  - Local storage is handled by [lib/services/storage.dart](mdc:lib/services/storage.dart)

- **Widgets Layer**: The `lib/widgets` directory contains reusable UI components.
  - Game-specific widgets are in the `lib/widgets/game` subdirectory
  - Common UI elements are in the `lib/widgets/common` subdirectory